<TITLE> Ex-MP Salauddin's son gets 7 years for tax-dodge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  Tanveer Ahmed, the youngest son of former BNP lawmaker Salauddin Ahmed, Wednesday was convicted of three counts of tax-dodge charges and jailed for seven years. Since the terms will run concurrently, he will serve a total of five years in jail, judge Md Ashraf Hossain of Special Judge's Court-5 said in his verdict. The three-term verdict handed down five years for concealing wealth information, one year for not filing income tax return and another year for falsifying information on his income tax return. The judgement would come in force from the date of arrest or surrender of the convict, who is absconding. The judge also fined Tanveer Tk 8 lakh or said the convict would face another one and a half years in jail on failure to pay the fine. The National Board of Revenue filed a case on Oct 1, charging Tanveer with concealing over Tk 30 lakh in earnings in his income tax returns submitted through two consecutive years and failing to submit tax return for the 2006-2007. Tanveer's mother and brotherboth abscondingwere sentenced each to eight years in jail for tax evasion on Nov 5. bdnews24.com
